{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01UshvGu6KaTQBxifBz5WuyL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The AI Flow Builder fetches and decrypts per-org API keys via `getApiKey` in `server/services/ai/agent-executor.ts:118`:\n\n1. **Tenant-scoped lookup** — queries the `credentials` table with `and(eq(credentials.id, credentialId), eq(credentials.organizationId, organizationId))`, so a credential row only resolves when both IDs match (prevents cross-org access).\n2. **Decrypt the config blob** — calls `decryptObject<{ apiKey: string; baseUrl?: string }>(cred.config)` from `lib/encryption.ts`.\n3. **Return** `{ apiKey, baseUrl }` to the executor, which hands it to the OpenAI/Anthropic SDK client.\n\n**Helper function:** `decryptObject` (`lib/encryption.ts:71`) — a thin generic wrapper that calls `decrypt` (`lib/encryption.ts:40`) and `JSON.parse`s the result. `decrypt` itself does AES-GCM decryption: splits the stored `iv:authTag:ciphertext` triple, builds a decipher with `crypto.createDecipheriv(ALGORITHM, key, iv)`, sets the auth tag, and returns the plaintext.\n\nSo the short answer: **`decryptObject`** (backed by `decrypt`) in `lib/encryption.ts`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":18039,"cache_read_input_tokens":19320,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":18039},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"62967185-13dd-45d6-837b-7a213340a7ff","uuid":"cf7a7e31-8704-40f3-89d2-047b3afb28d4"}
